A gimmicky map, intended for gun game, but probably usable in other modes.

3 small rooms, with a large door seperating 2 the sides, across the center of each.
The door opens automatically for a few seconds, so you should take cover and shoot whatever you see.
Then a few seconds with the doors closed to change position if you want, then open again. You can not go through the dorway during this period.
So think of it like a little shooting range where the targets move around between rounds.

After 5 goes (one minute), the doors stay open, and you can cross to the other side to finish the other team off! (And get your knife)

GG_FY_SNOWBUNKER_V2

Maximum Players: 64
Recommened Players: 12-32

This map takes place somewhere in the snow, with two bunkers on either side. In the middle, there is a "no man's land", complete with some walls, logs, and boxes. The roofs to both buildings are accessible, and connected by a bridge. Underground, which is accessable from the bunkers, there's a long hallway that can house a small skirmish and two vents on either side that can be used to sneak into the enemy bunker.

It's been a while since I've updated this map, as it was one of the first ones I have ever made for the Source engine. I've completely redesigned it and redid most of the map, optimizing it and making it look a lot nicer than it did before. 

Players will find they get well over 100FPS, even with 24 players, in-game. I worked hard to ensure this stays true. If the map is running without any players, I get a solid 250FPS or above in 90% of the areas on the map.

Comments, questions, suggestions, and complaints are welcome.
Assessments are welcome as well.

Thanks for viewing and enjoy! =D
